Effective date: February 14, 2024

This Privacy Policy describes how your personal information is collected, used, and shared when you install or use the Tic Tac Toe game (hereinafter referred to as "the Game") on your device. This policy is designed to meet the compliance standards of the Google Play Store and to ensure the protection of your data.

1. Personal Information We Do Not Collect
The Game does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information of its users. As a non-commercial, free-to-play application, Tic Tac Toe is designed to respect your privacy and personal data. The Game does not require registration, and we do not have access to information such as names, email addresses, phone numbers, or any other personal details.

2. No Third-Party Data Sharing
Since the Game does not collect personal information, there is no data to share with third parties. We are committed to ensuring the privacy and security of our users.

3. No Data Storage
The Game does not store any data, personal or otherwise, on any servers or databases. All game progress and settings are stored locally on your device and can be removed at any time by uninstalling the Game.

4. Children's Privacy
Tic Tac Toe complies with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. Since no personal information is collected from any user, the Game is deemed suitable for all ages.

5. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update or change our Privacy Policy at any time. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.

6. Your Consent
By using the Game, you are consenting to our Privacy Policy and agree to its terms.

7. Contact Us
If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us at: garley.apps@gmail.com

